member.summary:
Helper class for comparaison of objects.
The idea is to use this class for chaining comparaison by leveraging the null-coalesing operator.
e.g.


public int Compare(T first, T second)
{
    return ComparerHelper.ReferenceCompare(first, second) ??                       //Null so references are different, fallback to the other check
           ComparerHelper.Compare(first.SomeProperty, second.SomeProperty) ??      //Null so values equals, fallback to the other check
           ComparerHelper.Compare(first.id, second.id, FairGuidComparer.Default) ??//Null so values are equals, fallback to the other check
           ComparerHelper.EQUALS;                                                  //No more check we return EQUALS(0)
}

